  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And for those that worked in this agriculture on the field, the Germans gave us a little plot.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the irony is you plant it, you nurture it and you watch it grow, and then overnight somebody else came and pulled out the potatoes or the carrots that you had.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So you never had a yield from whatever you tried to plant.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The reason that I had access to that, because in my work I had access to the seeds.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now the most important thing, and I first, according to the German Criminal Act, was that you normally wore knickers, knickerbockers, because you had to work snow, and you only had one set of clothing.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You don't have-- you know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The beauty of it was that you could bring your socks over the knickerbockers and make a baggy look, and I would proceed to steel beans or dried peas-- anything that would plant-- and you have to go every night through German inspection.",
      "word_count": 43
    }
  ],
